frameDefinitions: An Item comes to be attached to a Goal, with a Connector forming a bond between the Handle of the Item and the Goal (or some part of it).
An Entity is declared to exist, generally irrespective of its position or even the possibility of its position being specified.
This frame contains words that describe specific aspects of a Color.
Despite some implication that a State would be interrupted, the Entity remains in the specified State.
A Process of using or modifying is scheduled to be applied to a group or mass.
A perceptible Figure shows up against a Ground location due to Light shining on/from it, its salience possibly dependent on a Cause_of_shine.
frameExamples: According to plan, the front part of the hull quietly <t>attached</t> to the docking gear.
Finally, Poland ceased to <t>exist</t> as a state for hundreds of years.
Three more cars <t>remain</t> to be fixed.
listRoleDefinitions: <fen>Connector</fen> identifies the  instrument used to attach, usually in a <ment>with</ment>-PP.
<fen>Item</fen> identifies the entity that comes to be attached to the <fen>Goal</fen>.
<fen>Items</fen> identifies the plural items that are tied together, resulting in their mutual attachment.
<fen>Goal</fen> identifies the location to which the first <fen>Item</fen> is attached.
The time when the attaching event takes place.
The location where the attaching event takes place.
Some entity, abstract or concrete, which is stated to exist.
A time at which the entity is in existence.
Where the <fen>Entity</fen> exists.
The color that is being described.
The entity whose <fen>Color</fen> is being described.
A concrete or abstract <fen>Entity</fen>.
The <fen>State</fen> of an <fen>Entity</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>State</fen> is found to still persist.
The location where the <fen>Entity</fen> is in the <fen>State</fen>.
The activity that is being applied to the mass or the set of entities.
The mass or group that has not yet been processed.
The time when the <fen>Remainder</fen> is assessed.
The percept which is perceived at a certain <fen>Ground</fen> location.
The location of the phenomenon.
The <fen>Light</fen> which is emitted.  In this frame, it is usually incorporated in verbs and adjectives, and is the denotation of many of the nouns.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Figure</fen> is observed against the <fen>Ground</fen> location due to <fen>Light</fen> shining on it.
The spatial setting in which the <fen>Figure</fen> shows up against a <fen>Ground</fen> location.
listRoleExamples: The remoras attach to the whale <fex>with their strong jaws</fex>.
The remoras attach <fex>to the underside of the whale</fex>.
Fornalutx is a jewel of warm <fex>stone</fex>.
Martial law remains in effect <fex>in Absurdistan</fex>.
An additional eighty-three invitations remain <fex>to be sent</fex>
In this case everyone should be informed by word of mouth to contact the person holding the list to find out <fex>which gifts</fex> still remain to be bought.
<fex>Now</fex> only three more items remain to be sold
Hot coals glowed <fex>behind the fire grate</fex>.
<fex>In the morning</fex> the grass glistened with dew
<fex>Outside</fex> something was shimmering on the shore.
